text: Wonderful vidhi (recipe) to make bhoga for Thakurji! Mishri is very pure, sacred and highly beneficial! One should always use it or jaggery where possible instead of refined sugar! Fantastic recipe...I always adore the presence of paneer in a milk-based mithai...One can shape it like a peda to make a lovely peda :-) One can use almond-cashew milk, coconut cream, soy-peanut milk paneer (there's a video for it), cashew-coconut-soy milk powders (find them online- Organic Traditions), steam-refined coconut oil and mishri....I'd love to see a vegan, dairy-free, wholly plant-based recipe for peda or dairy-free milk burfi based on these ingredients if possible someday (Though I've made it and it was pretty fantastic and just like dairy, it'd be great to see a experienced/professional/expert make it)...thank you kindly :-)
author: Arika Tank
